[12:14] <eveo> .tell parv that's entirely incorrect tho, which is why it's best not to guess. &{Str.NFC}.signature gives you a block that calls Str.NFC and you're calling signature on that block. You could stick anything into that block and still get the same signature. The correct way is Str.^lookup('NFC').candidatesÂ».signature. You should use .candidates bit for subs too, otherwise you only get the sig of the proto

